Figure 1 illustrates a toy example of the sampling scheme for the set of 12 samples gathered in 6 pools, where each sample is included in two pools (i.e. n=12, m=6, k=2). The pooling is represented as a bipartite graph, and the corresponding pooling matrix Φ is shown. The pooling schemes proposed by Sinnott-Armstrong et al. and Eberhardt et al. could be considered as specific instances of the proposed pooling scheme where k=2 and k=1 respectively.
